  <div class="detail-grid">
    <div class="detail-section full ab">
      <div class="slabel">◎ Overview</div>
      <p class="stext" style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.9;">A fully autonomous line-maze-solving robot built on the Pololu 3pi+ (ATmega32U4) platform. Implements PID line-following, a left-hand rule FSM for intersection decision-making, and path-reduction algorithms to optimize second-run traversal.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="margin-top:2px;" class="detail-grid">
    <div class="detail-section ab2">
      <div class="slabel">⊙ System Objective</div>
      <p class="stext">Design, implement, and validate a real-time embedded control system capable of navigating an unknown line maze, recording the full decision path during exploration, applying path-reduction to compute the shortest route, and executing the optimized second run without entering any dead ends.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="detail-section">
      <div class="slabel">⊘ Design Constraints</div>
      <div class="spec-list"><div class="spec-item">All firmware must execute on the ATmega32U4 at 16 MHz with no OS; all timing must be software-managed</div><div class="spec-item">PID loop must run fast enough to maintain line tracking at navigating speeds without CPU saturation</div><div class="spec-item">FSM must resolve ambiguous intersections (straight-or-right, straight-or-left) using inch-forward sensing</div><div class="spec-item">Path array is statically allocated — buffer overflow must be prevented at compile time</div><div class="spec-item">Path-reduction algorithm must handle all three-step patterns (L-U-L, L-U-S, L-U-R, S-U-S) in multi-pass</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="margin-top:2px;">
    <div class="detail-section full">
      <div class="slabel">⊞ System Architecture</div>
      <div class="arch-diagram">┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
